rComments: I wasnt particularly interested in aging at first but Dr. Galarneau made it fun and interesting. I liked the format of the evaluations. 3 exams and 4 discussion forums to complete. No big project.

Great teacher. The classes are interactive. The DSM5 mental disorders are presented clearly. Prof Galarneau is caring and it shows that she wants her students to do well. The clinical vignettes given as assignments are also interesting. Thumps up for me! :)

Prof Bégin was one of the best profs I've had! I highly recommend taking her classes. If I remember correctly, she really values participation and engaging students in discussions during her lectures.

Prof Begin tends to read her PPT. Makes a lot of mistakes when she writes her exams and the paper is long (present the material about the different types of personalities just before the deadline for the paper???)

So confusing she's all over the place with her powerpoints, you can't follow along. Think you've studied hard and did well on the exam? Just kidding you'll only get a B+. She also seems to forget that we're students with multiple classes and says we need to be organized but she claims she's always busy and also needs someone to remind her of time??
Teaches just fine, but can be a bit rude and make you feel stupid when she answers your questions. To me thats a huge turn off, but if that doesn't bother you she's fine as a teacher, easy class.
Prof Begin Galarneau is really nice. Her class was really interesting, even if she tends to read her PPT. Read the textbook and you'll be fine 2 midterms easy + 1 paper + 1 final.
